DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "extraAnswerEvaluators.pl");

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(2,5,1);
$b1 = random(2,5,1);
$x0 = $b1*$b1;
$y0 = $b1 + $a1;
$x1 = $x0 + 0.1;
$sx1= sqrt($x1);
$x01 = $x0 + 0.01;
$sx01= sqrt($x01);
$x9 =  $x0 - 0.1;
$sx9= sqrt($x9);
$x99 = $x0- 0.01;
$sx99= sqrt($x99);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
The point \( P($x0 , $y0 ) \) lies on the curve
\( y = \sqrt{  x } + $a1 \).  If \( Q \) is the point
\( (x, \sqrt{ x }+ $a1 ) \), find the slope of the secant line
\( PQ \) for the following values of \( x \).
$BR
If \( x= $x1 \), the slope of \( PQ \) is:
\{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans =1/($b1 + $sx1 );
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and if \( x= $x01 \), the slope of \( PQ \) is:
\{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans =1/($b1 + $sx01 );
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and if \( x= $x9 \), the slope of \( PQ \) is:
\{ans_rule(25)  \}
$BR
EOT

$ans =1/($b1 +  $sx9 );
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and if \( x= $x99 \), the slope of \( PQ \) is:
\{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans =1/($b1 + $sx99);
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Based on the above results, guess the slope of the tangent
line to the curve at \( P($x0 , $y0 ) \).
\{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans =1/(2* $b1 );
ANS(num_cmp($ans, relTol=>4));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
